      "side": 1,
      "message": "just to make sure i understand, there are two NewForwarder functions now: this c\u0027tor, and the method on SSH. the signature that you quoted above is used for the method on SSH, but it can\u0027t be used here -- we\u0027d need to also take a *SSH arg.\n\nwhat about just renaming this function to newForwarder, so that the only exported way to create a Forwarder is via SSH.NewForwarder? the (over-)generalization still seems nice from a unit-testing perspective, and part of me thought that supporting non-SSH media could be useful in the future. i think we\u0027ve talked about adb implementations in the past, and i\u0027ve also thought about having a local impl of SSH\u0027s interface to make it possible to use the same code in either local or remote tests. still not sure if that\u0027s a good idea :-P",
